fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data

Interface IFetchable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAttachable, ICellStructure, IListStructure
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IIntersection, ISource

    public interface IFetchable
extends IAttachable, ICellStructure, IListStructure
    Defines the basic API for fetching data from a data source or a composite intersection.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent read/write access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • fetchItem

        default IItem fetchItem(ITicket usingTicket,
                        IKey key)
                 throws ItemFetchException,
                        AuthzException
        Fetches the specified item for the specified ticket, if the user is authorized and a match can be found using the specified key.

        It is assumed that best performance is sought when invoking this method, so it is equivalent to calling fetchItem(usingTicket,key,EnumSet.allOf(Defer.class) (in other words, anything that can be deferred will be deferred).

        Parameters:
        usingTicket - authenticates the user performing the request.
        key - the key identifying the item.
        Returns:
        the item, if found, or null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the key does not apply to this source.
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ItemFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0

      • fetchItem

        IItem fetchItem(ITicket usingTicket,
                IKey key,
                EnumSet<Defer> defer)
         throws ItemFetchException,
                AuthzException
        Fetches the specified item for the specified ticket, if the user is authorized and a match can be found using the specified key, and optionally deferring retrieval of certain categories of data.
        Parameters:
        usingTicket - authenticates the user performing the request.
        key - the key identifying the item.
        defer - the categories of data to fetch lazily (on demand). If null, is equivalent to EnumSet.allOf(Defer.class).
        Returns:
        the item, if found, or null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the key does not apply to this source.
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ItemFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0

      • fetchList

        default IList fetchList(ITicket usingTicket,
                        IFilter filter,
                        ISort sort,
                        IRange range)
                 throws ListFetchException,
                        AuthzException
        Fetches a list of item references in the specified range matching the specified filter with the specifed sorting rules, as authorized by the privileges of the specified ticket.

        It is assumed that best performance is sought when invoking this method, so it is equivalent to calling fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range,EnumSet.allOf(Defer.class) (in other words, anything that can be deferred will be deferred).

        Parameters:
        usingTicket - authenticates the user performing the request.
        filter - the filter for items to select, or null.
        sort - the sorting rules for items to select, or null.
        range - the range of items to select, or null (if null, all items are fetched, which may lead to performance issues). The contents of the range will also depend on any defined filter or sort.
        Returns:
        the list. Never returns null, may return an empty list.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the filter, sort or range do not apply to this source.
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ListFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range,defer), fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range,fetchable)

      • fetchList

        IList fetchList(ITicket usingTicket,
                IFilter filter,
                ISort sort,
                IRange range,
                EnumSet<Defer> defer)
         throws ListFetchException,
                AuthzException
        Fetches a list of item references in the specified range matching the specified filter with the specifed sorting rules, as authorized by the privileges of the specified ticket, and optionally deferring retrieval of certain categories of data.
        Parameters:
        usingTicket - authenticates the user performing the request.
        filter - the filter for items to select, or null.
        sort - the sorting rules for items to select, or null.
        range - the range of items to select, or null (if null, all items are fetched, which may lead to performance issues). The contents of the range will also depend on any defined filter or sort.
        defer - the categories of data to fetch lazily (on demand). If null, is equivalent to EnumSet.allOf(Defer.class).
        Returns:
        the list. Never returns null, may return an empty list.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the filter, sort or range do not apply to this source.
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ListFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range), fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range,fetchable)

      • fetchList

        IList fetchList(ITicket usingTicket,
                IFilter filter,
                ISort sort,
                IRange range,
                Set<ICell> fetchable)
         throws ListFetchException,
                AuthzException
        Fetches a list of item references in the specified range matching the specified filter with the specifed sorting rules, as authorized by the privileges of the specified ticket, initially retrieving only data for the specified set of cells.
        Parameters:
        usingTicket - authenticates the user performing the request.
        filter - the filter for items to select, or null.
        sort - the sorting rules for items to select, or null.
        range - the range of items to select, or null (if null, all items are fetched, which may lead to performance issues). The contents of the range will also depend on any defined filter or sort.
        fetchable - the fetchable data cells. All other data is fetched lazily (on demand). It is an error for this set to be null or empty.
        Returns:
        the list. Never returns null, may return an empty list.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the filter, sort or range do not apply to this source.
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ListFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range), fetchList(usingTicket,filter,sort,range,defer)

      • fetchCount

        long fetchCount(ITicket usingTicket,
                IFilter filter)
         throws FetchException
        Fetches the number of records that can be returned for this fetchable data set using the specified ticket and filter. Should not fetch the actual data.
        Parameters:
        usingTicket - authenticates the user performing the request.
        filter - the filter to use. May be null.
        Returns:
        the number of matching records.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the filter does not apply to this source.
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        FetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0

      • intersect

        IIntersection intersect(ISource relatedSource)
                 throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Creates an intersection from this data set A with another data set B, where the product contains only matching elements from both A and B as defined by the intersection predicate. This implies a default "Intersection.INNER" intersection type.
        Parameters:
        relatedSource - non-null the related data source.
        Returns:
        the resulting fetchable intersection.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if no such intersection can be provided by this connector for data sets A and B.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        intersect(ISource, Intersection)

        Parameters:

        intersectionType - the non-null intersection type.
        Returns:

        Throws:

        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
